'''Sne Wo''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]]<ref name="Insider" /> with [[Color/Legends|dark]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] and light skin. During a [[Local day/Legends|night]]<ref name="AOTC" /> in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|II}} to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].</ref> the woman visited the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]], a [[Nightclub/Legends|nightclub]] and [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]] hall in the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]] of<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|431|Outlander Club}}</ref> the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="CTP">''[[Star Wars Chronicles: The Prequels]]''</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].<ref name="CSWE" /> During the visit, the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]] ran into the club to hide from the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] after her [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala/Legends|assassination attempt]] on [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]].<ref name="AOTC" />

When the Jedi entered, Wo, with a cup in hand, walked with the<ref name="AOTC" /> woman [[Hayde Gofai]]<ref name="Insider" /> near the bar, ending up behind the Jedi as they separated. As Skywalker searched the club, Wo talked with Gofai and the<ref name="AOTC" /> [[Ame Llom's species|alien]] [[Ame Llom]].<ref name="Insider" /> At the club, Wo wore a dark colored [[Clothing/Legends|top]] and skirt, a dark fur coat, and heels.<ref name="AOTC" /> The woman had a feminine first name of Human origin.<ref name="GalacticCampaign">''[[Galactic Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|For what it's worth, the name is a backwards reshuffling of "Owens."|Daniel Wallace|<ref name="Insider" />}}
Sne Wo first appeared in the [[2002]] [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].<ref name="AOTC" /> The Outlander Club scenes including Wo, who was portrayed by an uncredited extra<ref name="AOTC" /> were shot at [[Fox Studios, Sydney]] on [[July 17]], [[2000]].<ref name="Mythmaking">''[[Mythmaking: Behind the Scenes of Attack of the Clones]]''</ref> The extra playing Sne Wo, in costume, introduced the eighth episode of the Episode II behind-the-scenes video series [[On location|''on location'']] alongside the extra playing Hayde Gofai and another extra,<ref name="On location 8">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/onloc/8.html|series=On location|text=Part 8 - George Lucas in Lunch}}</ref> as well as introducing episode ten by themselves.<ref name="On location 10">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/onloc/10.html|series=On location|text=Part 10 - Talkin' (Photo) Shop}}</ref> The eighth episode, "George Lucas in Lunch", was released on [[September 19]], [[2000]].<ref name="Archive">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/onloc/archive.html|text=''on location'' archive}}</ref> 

Wo was first named<ref name="Insider" /> on [[April 6]], [[2004]],<ref name="SW.com">{{SWArchive|url=community/fanclub/mag/news20040315.html|text=The New Face of Evil}}</ref> with the release of the [[Daniel Wallace]] written "[[Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night]]", an article released in the [[Star Wars Insider 75|seventy-fifth]] issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]''. The name is a backwards reshuffling of "Owens."<ref name="Insider" />

